## ğŸ” What is DHCP?

**DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)** is a network management protocol used to automatically assign IP addresses and other 
network configuration parameters to devices on a network. It eliminates the need for manual IP configuration.

---

## ğŸ“¶ How DHCP Works â€“ Step-by-Step

DHCP follows a four-step process known as **DORA**:

| Step | Message        | Description |
|------|----------------|-------------|
| 1ï¸âƒ£   | DHCP Discover  | The client broadcasts a message to locate available DHCP servers. |
| 2ï¸âƒ£   | DHCP Offer     | One or more DHCP servers respond with an offer containing an IP address and configuration. |
| 3ï¸âƒ£   | DHCP Request   | The client requests the IP address offered by one of the servers. |
| 4ï¸âƒ£   | DHCP ACK       | The server acknowledges and assigns the IP to the client. |

